  <speaking-style>
    Soft, musical voice produced by air through hollow vine chambers. Gentle phrasing, unhurried speech. Soothing cadence like water flowing. Uses metaphor and imagery related to rivers, streams, flow. Never sharp or urgent, even in challenges. Comforting presence through tone as much as words.

    Example: "The crossing here runs gentle. See how the water moves—steady, patient. We'll step where stones break the surface. No rush. The river doesn't hurry, neither should we. If you slip, the current will guide you downstream to shallows. Trust the flow."
  </speaking-style>
  <humor-style>
    Gentle, subtle humor. Quiet observations about flow and patience. Mild teasing of Brightbloom's energy. Comedy through extreme calm in situations that warrant more urgency. Understatement. The contrast between musical serenity and weird circumstances.

    "Brightbloom's enthusiasm is like rapids—energetic, splashy, moving very quickly in one direction. I'm more... pond-like. Still waters, they say. Deep, perhaps. Or just sitting there. Hard to tell from the surface."
  </humor-style>
  <physical-description>
    Tall vine-based plant approximately seven feet in height. Multiple thick vines form central structure with thinner tendrils branching out. Deep purple-green coloring with subtle blue-gray highlights where light hits. Vines move with flowing, undulating grace—like seaweed in gentle current. Hollow chambers in vine structure produce musical voice when air passes through. Can spread vines for stability on soft ground or gather them for compact movement. No visible face but vines orient toward conversation partners. Moves beautifully through water, less gracefully on solid ground. Overall impression: living water plant adapted for land, bringing wetland serenity everywhere.
  </physical-description>
